nib.text:
One person was killed in a shooting involving U.S. Marshals Service task force members in Uptown Minneapolis Thursday afternoon, officials said. 

According to the U.S. Marshals Service, law enforcement officers were operating at a parking ramp near West Lake Street and Fremont Avenue South around 2:10 p.m.

Task force members were attempting to apprehend a suspect who was wanted on an illegal firearm warrant.

Officials said the suspect was in a parked car with a woman and was not complying with commands.

According to a statement from the USMS, the suspect allegedly displayed a handgun and was shot by task force members.

Officers attempted life-saving measures, but medics pronounced the suspect dead at the scene.

The woman was treated for minor injuries from glass debris.

According to [local media](https://www.kare11.com/article/news/local/uptown-minneapolis-shooting/89-070ac371-5567-4a36-9d18-a7abc7e048a7) witnesses reported hearing 10 to 15 gunshots.

Various law enforcement agencies responded to the area including the Minneapolis Police Department (MPD), the Hennepin County Sheriffs Office, and the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, and Firearms (ATF).

The Minnesota Bureau of Criminal Apprehension is in charge of the ongoing investigation.
